With curvaceous coupe and roadster body styles and a lot of high-performance tech, the Mercedes-AMG GT is stunning to look at and exciting to drive

cars.name: Nissan GTR

cars.name: Audi A4
cars.description: The base specification rose to 201 hp and 236 lb-ft of torque, and the upgraded unit's output increased to 261 hp and 273 lb-ft of torque.

cars.name: BMW M3
cars.description: M3 sedan features a twin-turbo 3.0-liter inline-six. The normal version sends 473 horsepower and 406 pound-feet of torque

cars.name: Toyota Brz
cars.description: With a 2.4-liter, 228 hp BOXER engine, 182 pound-feet of torque, and track-tuned suspension, the BRZ is a high-performance sports car for demanding drivers.

cars.name: Golf GTR
cars.description: The Golf Mk7 GTI is powered by a 2.0-litre turbocharged direct-injection petrol engine (TSI) with 220 PS (162 kW; 217 hp). In the GTI Performance version, the engine's maximum power is boosted to 230 PS (169 kW; 227 hp). Both GTI models develop 350 N⋅m (36 kg⋅m; 258 lb⋅ft) of torque.
